            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.06169/2604.06169v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:The overall framework of our In-Place Test-Time Training. The module operates sequentially on input chunks. For each chunk, the current fast weights are firstappliedto the intermediate activations𝐙\\mathbf{Z}to produce the output. Then, these weights areupdatedusing the activations𝐙\\mathbf{Z}and a value𝐕\\mathbf{V}derived from the token embeddings. This \"apply-then-update\" cycle allows the model to dynamically adapt to incoming context in a strictly causal manner.",
                "position": 506
            }
